<subSubSection id="9F826578E17CFFF8FF3D1203FEE3F8C5" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D72736F3E17CFFF8FF3D1203FEE3F8C5" blockId="36.[151,1437,153,1971]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="E5ECEAE1E17CFFF8FF3D1203FED9F8EE" bold="true" box="[199,338,1833,1859]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology:</emphasis>
Species named after the astrophysicist Stephen W. Hawking (
<date id="A3261033E17CFFF8FC041203FB0AF8EE" box="[1022,1153,1833,1859]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1942" valueMax="2018">1942–2018</date>
), one of the most brilliant minds of all times.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9F826578E17CFFF8FF3D1259FCF8F81E" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D72736F3E17CFFF8FF3D1259FCF8F81E" blockId="36.[151,1437,153,1971]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="E5ECEAE1E17CFFF8FF3D1259FED9F823" bold="true" box="[199,338,1907,1934]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Comments:</emphasis>
Rare species that appears to be endemic to northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="AF8F7663E17CFFF8FC331259FB9BF820" box="[969,1040,1907,1933]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, although it is known from two different ecoregions there—the Atlantic rainforest and the Caatinga.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
